b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Boomy is best suited for releasing music to Spotify/Apple Music, casual music creators, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. ElevenLabs, meanwhile, shines for content creators needing realistic voices, audiobook production, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2019, Boomy describes itself as \"Create and release AI music to streaming platforms.\" ElevenLabs, established in 2022, positions itself as \"The most realistic AI text-to-speech and voice cloning.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **ElevenLabs** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 5.0), more features (6 vs 1), more competitive pricing, availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Boomy is a poor choice — far from it. Boomy excels in its own right, particularly for releasing music to Spotify/Apple Music and casual music creators.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class voice quality, go with ElevenLabs. If direct spotify/apple music distribution matters more to you, Boomy is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
